---
import HereticTick from './HereticTick.astro';
---

<section class="bg-parchment-texture py-16 md:py-24 px-4 text-center">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <h1
      class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-6xl font-black text-parchment mb-6 leading-tight"
      style="text-shadow: 0 2px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);"
    >
      Are You a <span class="text-gold">Heretic</span>?<HereticTick size="lg" />
    </h1>
    <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-parchment/70 mb-4 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      Every Christian is &mdash; according to someone. Take the quiz to find out which councils would condemn you.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base text-parchment/50 mb-8 max-w-xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
      If you've ever wondered "Am I a heretic?" &mdash; the answer might surprise you.
      The question isn't <em>whether</em> you hold views some council condemned.
      It's how many councils, and which ones. The truth has nothing to fear from honest questions.
    </p>
    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
      <a
        href="/quiz"
        class="inline-block px-8 py-4 bg-gold text-charcoal font-bold rounded-xl text-lg hover:bg-gold-light transition-colors shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl font-display"
      >
        Am I a Heretic? Take the Quiz
      </a>
      <a
        href="/explore"
        class="inline-block px-8 py-4 border border-parchment/30 text-parchment font-semibold rounded-xl text-lg hover:border-gold hover:text-gold transition-colors"
      >
        Explore Heresies
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="py-16 px-4 bg-parchment">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
    <h2
      class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-charcoal"
    >
      Every Christian Is a Heretic According to Someone
    </h2>
    <p class="text-lg text-charcoal/70 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      This heresy quiz doesn't test whether you're orthodox &mdash; it reveals that "orthodox" is a moving target.
      Over 2,000 years, church councils have questioned virtually every position a thoughtful Christian might hold.
      Trinitarians were heretics in the 4th century. Protestants are still under anathema from Trent.
      Catholics are heretics according to the Synod of Dort. This Christian theology quiz maps your beliefs
      against the real rulings of real councils &mdash; and shows you which ones would have condemned you.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
